<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Widespread throughout the Indo-Pacific including Mozambique (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4359.1.1" author="Tibirica, Y" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 133" refId="B252" refString="Tibirica, Y, Pola, M, Cervera, JL, 2017. Astonishing diversity revealed: an annotated and illustrated inventory of Nudipleura (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) from Mozambique. Zootaxa 4359: 1 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4359.1.1" title="Astonishing diversity revealed: an annotated and illustrated inventory of Nudipleura (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) from Mozambique." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4359.1.1" volume="4359" year="2017">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tibiriçá">Tibirica</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
), Tanzania, New Caledonia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1985.tb00875.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="241 - 299" refId="B214" refString="Rudman, WB, 1985. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Chromodoris aureomarginata, C. verrieri and C. fidelis colour groups. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 83: 241 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1985.tb00875.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Chromodoris aureomarginata, C. verrieri and C. fidelis colour groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1985.tb00875.x" volume="83" year="1985">Rudman 1985</bibRefCitation>
), Australia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/RS16011" author="Nimbs, M" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="44 - 113" refId="B176" refString="Nimbs, M, Smith, S, 2016. An illustrated inventory of the sea slugs of New South Wales, Australia (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia). Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria 128: 44 - 113, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/RS16011" title="An illustrated inventory of the sea slugs of New South Wales, Australia (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia)." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/RS16011" volume="128" year="2016">Nimbs and Smith 2016</bibRefCitation>
), South Africa, Madagascar, Indonesia, Philippines, Hawaii (
<bibRefCitation author="Gosliner, TM" journalOrPublisher="Sea Challengers Natural History Books, Gig Harbor" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B94" refString="Gosliner, TM, Behrens, D, Valdes, A, 2008. Indo-Pacific nudibranchs and sea slugs: a field guide to the world's most diverse fauna. Sea Challengers Natural History Books, Gig Harbor" title="Indo-Pacific nudibranchs and sea slugs: a field guide to the world's most diverse fauna." year="2008">Gosliner et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), and Red Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Saudi Arabia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="290 - 309" refId="B280" refString="Yonow, N, 1989. Red Sea Opisthobranchia. 2. The family Chromodorididae (Mollusca, Nudibranchia). Fauna of Saudi Arabia 10: 290 - 309" title="Red Sea Opisthobranchia. 2. The family Chromodorididae (Mollusca, Nudibranchia)." volume="10" year="1989">Yonow 1989</bibRefCitation>
